==English==

===Etymology===
From Turkish [[ibrik#Turkish|ibrik]] ‘ewer’; (in Arabic {{ARchar|[[إبريق]]}} ''‘ibrīq''); (in Farsi {{FAchar|[[ابريق]]}} ''ābrīq'')
===Pronunciation===
* {{IPA|/ɪb'ri:k/}}

===Noun===
{{en-noun}}
# A long-spouted pitcher, typically made of brass. Occasionally confused with a Turkish coffee pot, which is properly called "cezve"(sometimes spelled "jezve")




